# Markdown Decomposition in nyne

## How Markdown Files Decompose

Markdown files are recursively decomposed at headers. Each section becomes a virtual file
that can be read, edited, or reordered independently.

```
doc.md@/symbols/OVERVIEW.md                        # section listing with token estimates
doc.md@/symbols/10-introduction.md                 # first section
doc.md@/symbols/20-getting-started.md              # second section
doc.md@/symbols/20-getting-started/                # nested subsections (if any)
doc.md@/symbols/20-getting-started/10-install.md   # nested subsection
```

## Section Naming

Section filenames use 10-increment numeric prefixes derived from document order.
The text portion is derived from the header text, lowercased and hyphenated.

Read `OVERVIEW.md` or `ls @/symbols/` to discover exact names — don't guess them.

## Code Block Extraction

Fenced code blocks within sections are extracted as editable files:

```
doc.md@/symbols/20-getting-started/code/10.rs    # first ```rust block
doc.md@/symbols/20-getting-started/code/20.sh    # second ```sh block
doc.md@/symbols/20-getting-started/code/30.txt   # unlabeled fence (no language tag)
```

Extensions come from the fence language tag. Unlabeled blocks get `.txt`.

## Reading Markdown Efficiently

### Exploration pattern

```sh
# 1. Get section overview
cat doc.md@/symbols/OVERVIEW.md

# 2. Read specific section
cat doc.md@/symbols/30-phase-3.md

# 3. Read a code example from that section
cat doc.md@/symbols/30-phase-3/code/10.rs
```

### Searching across sections

```sh
# Find which sections mention a topic
grep -l "caching" doc.md@/symbols/*.md

# Search within code blocks
grep -r "unwrap()" doc.md@/symbols/*/code/*.rs
```

## Editing Markdown Sections

### Rewrite a section

Write to the section file to replace its content:

```sh
# Replace section content (header is preserved)
echo "New content here" > doc.md@/symbols/20-getting-started.md
```

### Reorder sections

Rename the numeric prefix to change order:

```sh
mv doc.md@/symbols/50-appendix.md doc.md@/symbols/20-appendix.md
```

All sections are renumbered to maintain consistent 10-increments after a reorder.

### Edit code blocks

Code blocks are writable — edits splice back into the original markdown:

```sh
# Edit a code example directly
echo 'fn main() { println!("fixed"); }' > doc.md@/symbols/20-getting-started/code/10.rs
```

Blocks that parse cleanly are validated by tree-sitter on write. Partial/incomplete
snippets skip validation.

## OVERVIEW.md for Markdown

The overview includes:
- Section hierarchy with nesting depth
- Token estimates per section
- Code block inventory per section (count and languages)

Use the code block inventory to find examples without reading every section.
